Privacy Policy for BAS HeroLast Updated: June 25, 2025[Your Company Name] ("us", "we", or "our") operates the BAS Hero web application (the "Service"). This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service and the choices you have associated with that data.We use your data to provide and improve the Service. By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.1. Information Collection and UseWe collect several different types of information for various purposes to provide and improve our Service to you.Types of Data Collected:Personal Data: While using our Service, we may ask you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you ("Personal Data"). This may include, but is not limited to:Email addressFirst name and last name (or username)Financial Data: To use the core features of the Service, you will upload or manually enter financial information. This includes:PDF documents such as bank statements, Uber summaries, or DiDi summaries.Manually entered income and expense transactions.Logbook entries, including trip details and odometer readings.Vehicle cost and purchase date for depreciation calculations.Usage Data: We may also collect information on how the Service is accessed and used ("Usage Data"). This Usage Data may include information such as your computer's Internet Protocol address (e.g. IP address), browser type, browser version, the pages of our Service that you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on those pages, unique device identifiers and other diagnostic data.2. Use of Data[Your Company Name] uses the collected data for various purposes:To provide and maintain the Service.To manage your account and subscription.To perform the core functions of the app, such as calculating your BAS summary and weekly profit/loss.To provide customer support.To monitor the usage of the Service to improve its functionality.Use of Data with AI Services:Certain features, such as the AI-powered bank statement scanner, require sending the text content of your uploaded documents to a third-party AI service (Google's Gemini API) for processing. We only send the raw text needed for the feature to function. We do not send your Personal Data (like your name or email) along with this content. The AI's use of this data is governed by Google's privacy policies.3. Data Storage and SecurityThe security of your data is important to us. All your personal and financial data is stored securely in Google Firebase's Firestore database. We use industry-standard security measures to protect your information. However, remember that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.4. Data Sharing and DisclosureWe do not sell or rent your Personal Data to third parties. We may disclose your data in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to:To comply with a legal obligation.To protect and defend the rights or property of [Your Company Name].To prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the Service.To protect the personal safety of users of the Service or the public.5. Third-Party Service ProvidersWe may employ third-party companies and individuals to facilitate our Service ("Service Providers"), to provide the Service on our behalf, or to assist us in analyzing how our Service is used. These third parties have access to your Personal Data only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.Google Firebase: For database hosting, user authentication, and web hosting.Google Gemini API: For AI-powered features.[e.g., Lemon Squeezy or Stripe]: For processing subscription payments.6. Your Data RightsYou have the right to access, update, or delete the information we have on you. Within your account, you can add, update, or delete transactions and logbook entries at any time. If you wish to permanently delete your account and all associated data, please contact us.7. Changes to This Privacy PolicyWe may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.8. Contact UsIf you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:By email: [support@bashero.com]
